title: Internet resources
extract: Internet resource locators, described in RFC 1736, convey location and access information for resources. Typical examples of resources include network accessible documents, WAIS databases, FTP servers, and Telnet destinations. ... An Internet resource locator is a locator defined by an Internet resource location standard.
